text: Nainital is a town in the Indian state of Uttarakhand and headquarters of Nainital district in the Kumaon foothills of the outer Himalayas. Naini Lake has too low a level of oxygen in the bottom layer to sustain fish. This is mostly due to pollution, which includes illegal dumping of garbage. == Other websites == * Trade Guide for Nainital District Category:Towns in India Category:Settlements in Uttarakhand
